INT. FRONTIER MISSION CONTROL - NIGHT

The floor quiet and full. On the main screen, the ship's track curls away from the Earth line toward a drawn gray circle.

FLIGHT DIRECTOR:
Flight controllers, go no-go for trans-lunar injection. Guidance.

CONTROLLER (O.S.):
Go.

FLIGHT DIRECTOR:
Propulsion.

CONTROLLER #2 (O.S.): Go.

FLIGHT DIRECTOR:
Harmony One, you are go for TLI.

In the glass VIP row, Vess stands alone at the rail. Behind her, Pell works through a commemorative program with a highlighter.

BRANDT (V.O.):
(on the loop)
Copy. Go for TLI.

INT. HARMONY ONE, CARGO BAY - CONTINUOUS

The bay in standby glow. Four amber lights at four vent slits.

A clunk through the structure. Then the push — long and gathering — straps creaking taut against the crates.

INT. CRATE D - CONTINUOUS

Cricket pressed back into the couch, the amber light steady, his hand flat on the lid. The burn goes on. And on.

Then: cutoff. Weightless again. The kit bag floats up to the end of its lanyard.

INT. CRATE C - CONTINUOUS

Dutch, pencil out, runs figures in the notebook margin — velocity, a time, an arc — and boxes the result, twice.

INSERT — THE NOTEBOOK: BURN NOMINAL. COAST 62 HRS. NO ABORT MODES REMAIN.

He looks at the boxed line a moment. Then he knocks on his crate wall: two — two.

Two — two, from D. Two — two, from B. Two — two, from A.

INT. FRONTIER MISSION CONTROL - CONTINUOUS

The track on the main screen bends out of Earth's neighborhood for good. Applause on the floor, brief and professional.

Vess watches the line go. She lets go of the rail, one finger at a time.

FLIGHT DIRECTOR:
Trajectory nominal. Sixty-two hours to lunar orbit insertion, gentlemen. Get some sleep.

Pell caps his highlighter.

PELL:
Well. Nothing stopping it now.

Vess doesn't answer him.

CUT TO:

> **END OF ACT TWO** <
